@startuml UC-06_View_Analytics

title UC-06: View Usage Analytics

skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #E65100
skinparam ActivityFontColor #BF360C
skinparam ArrowColor #E65100

start
:User navigates to Analytics page;
:System displays dashboard loading state;
:AnalyticsService.get_dashboard_overview() called;
:Service aggregates data for selected period (default: Last 30 days);

:System displays dashboard sections:\n- KEY METRICS: Total Workflows, Active Workflows, Total Executions, Success Rate, Avg Execution Time\n- WORKFLOW PERFORMANCE: Each workflow's metrics, trends, last executed time\n- EXECUTION TRENDS: Line charts of executions per day, success vs failure\n- ERROR ANALYSIS: Most common errors, error rate by workflow, top failing nodes\n- INTEGRATION USAGE: Connected integrations count, API calls per integration\n- RESOURCE USAGE: Storage used/limit, API calls/limit, team members/limit;

:User can filter/customize view:\n- Time period picker (7d, 30d, 90d, custom)\n- Workflow selector (all or specific)\n- Status filter (all, success, failed)\n- Export options (CSV, JSON, PDF);

:User clicks on metric for details;
:System expands workflow performance breakdown;
:User views step-by-step execution logs;
:System renders all visualizations:\n- Charts (Chart.js/D3.js)\n- Tables with sorting/pagination\n- Cards with key metrics\n- Progress bars for resource usage;

:Real-time updates via WebSocket;
:Analytics logs "analytics_viewed" event;
:Dashboard fully loaded and interactive;
stop

@enduml
